info.headline: Dense Fog Advisory issued November 25 at 4:23AM EST until November 25 at 9:00AM EST by NWS Melbourne
info.description: ...DENSE FOG ADVISORY IN EFFECT UNTIL 9 AM THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Visibility one quarter mile or less in dense fog. * WHERE...Inland Volusia, Northern Lake, Orange, Seminole, Coastal Volusia and Southern Lake Counties. * WHEN...Until 9 AM this morning. * IMPACTS...Hazardous driving conditions due to low visibility. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Recent surface observations, satellite imagery and traffic cameras show areas of dense fog were reducing visibilities to one quarter mile or less across the advisory area, especially from Interstate 4 northward.
info.instruction: If you will be out driving early this morning, you may want to plan on leaving early, in order to give yourself plenty of time to safely reach y our destination. When driving in dense fog, reduce your speed, use only your low beam headlights, and leave plenty of distance between your vehicle and the one ahead of you.
